.TH challenged 1 "November 23, 2011" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "USER COMMANDS"
.SH NAME
challenged \- detect broken packages due to obsolete dependencies

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBchallenged\fR [option] ... \fIPackages file(s)\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B challenged 
performs a speculative analysis of the repository to identify those packages
that, if upgraded to a specific version, would break a large number of other
packages in the repository. This tool would be particularly useful during the
upgrade of a specific component to evaluate its impact on the software archive.
.P

.SH INPUT SPECIFICATION
The input of outdated is a list of Debian Packages files

.SH OUTPUT SPECIFICATION
The output of outdated is in the yaml format.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-b \-\-broken
Print the list of broken packages
.TP
.B \-d \-\-downgrade
Check package downgrades
.TP
.B \-c
Print the list of packages in a cluster
.TP
.B \-\-checkonly
Select a subset of packages to check. By default all packages are checked.
.TP
.B \-v
Enable info / warnings / debug messages. This option may be repeated
up to three times in order to increase verbosity.
.TP
.B \-\-progress
Enable progress bars.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display this list of options.

.SH EXAMPLE
challenged -v --progress Packages.bz2 > result.yaml

.SH NOTE

.SH AUTHOR
Pietro Abate and Roberto Di Cosmo

